<DOC><DOCNO> AP881018-0249 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-18-88 1129EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Phone     10-18 0299</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Phone,0310</SECOND><HEAD>MCI Earnings Up Nearly Six-Fold in 3rd-Qtr</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   MCI Communications Corp. said Tuesday itsearnings rose nearly six-fold in the third quarter on a 40.8percent rise in revenue.   MCI, the nation's second-largest long-distance company, said itsnet income rose to a record $99 million, or 38 cents per share, inthe three months ended Sept. 30 compared with $17 million, or 6cents per share, in 1987.   Third-quarter revenue rose to a record $1.4 billion for thequarter, compared with $994 million for the same period last year.   The company said earnings were driven by strong revenue growthfrom sales of 800-line and international services and gains incommercial accounts as well as improved operating margins.   ``Our success in increasing both volume and market share whilecontrolling costs has allowed us to take full advantage of the highoperating leverage that is fundamental to this industry,'' saidBert C. Roberts Jr., MCI president and chief operating officer.   MCI said the third quarter results included a pre-tax gain of$11 million from previously negotiated antitrust settlements and apre-tax charge of $8 million associated with a contract settlement.Results for the third quarter of 1987 included a pre-tax gain of $2million from antitrust settlements.   The results for this year's quarter also reflected a 7.35percent dividend on $400 million of preferred stock that was issuedto International Business Machines Corp. in August. MCI alsocompleted the repurchase of about 47 million shares of common stockfrom IBM.   For the nine months ended Sept. 30, MCI earnings rose more thanfivefold to $219 million, or 78 cents per share, from $41 million,or 14 cents per share, a year earlier.   Nine-month revenue rose 27.6 percent to $3.7 billion from $2.9billion a year earlier.</TEXT></DOC>